         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>
               Collection of sentences and sayings of Greek philosophers, Fathers of the Church and biblical figures. Some apophthegms are anonymous.
               The work was translated from the Arabic <t:foreign xml:lang="ar">Kitāb al-bustān wa-qāʿidat al-ḥukamāʾ wa-šams al-ʾādāb</t:foreign> between
               1510 and 1522 by <t:persName role="translator" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7077Mikael">Mikāʾel</t:persName> and enjoyed much popularity given the high number of manuscripts.
               There is a short and a long recension of the work. The <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7144MFTabiban">short recension</t:ref> generally
               preserves the Arabic text. The <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7145MFTabiban">long recension</t:ref> includes additional sayings of the Church Fathers
               and other stories, especially of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1499Ahiqar">Aḥiqar (Ḫikar)</t:persName>.</t:p>
            <t:p>
               <t:listBibl type="secondary">
